Concepts & Units
========================================================

- **Radiometry**: measurements of light in the physical world
- **Photometry**: measurements of light in the perceived world

***

<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Cartesian_Theater.svg/300px-Cartesian_Theater.svg.png" height="125%" width="125%" />


Luminous & Radiometric Power
========================================================

<img src = "https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRELyHPPEuOedMp_jeO3pc_85X9Z4xU9zObTQ&usqp=CAU" height="150%" width="150%" />

***

* **Luminous Power**
  + Total percieved light power emitted from a light source
  + Units: Lumens
* **Radiometric Power**:
  + Total emitted radiant energy from a radiant body
  + Units: Watts, J/sec


